Guianese Creole, Gwiyan**.

00:05:29.362 --> 00:05:29.862
You see?

00:05:29.862 --> 00:05:31.297
And then you can
understand them.

00:05:31.297 --> 00:05:32.131
You know, I can--

00:05:32.131 --> 00:05:33.499
when I went to
Mauritius, I could

00:05:33.499 --> 00:05:36.402
speak Creole in Mauritius, and
people could understand me.

00:05:36.402 --> 00:05:39.706
I could understand Mauritians
speaking Creole, so there is

00:05:39.706 --> 00:05:42.008
some evidence to Kreyolofoni--

00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:43.076
that there is a certain--

00:05:43.076 --> 00:05:46.012
there's some level of
mutual understanding.

00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:48.381
AUDIENCE: So that kind
colonized which countries,

00:05:48.381 --> 00:05:52.318
because [INAUDIBLE] talked
about the substrates?

