MICHEL DEGRAFF: The
[INAUDIBLE],, yeah.

00:05:54.253 --> 00:05:54.921
Yeah.

00:05:54.921 --> 00:05:57.256
AUDIENCE: Would that be
like of our practice?

00:05:57.256 --> 00:05:59.158
MICHEL DEGRAFF:
Definitely, you're right.

00:05:59.158 --> 00:06:01.160
You're right.

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:05.898
But it's thanks to the
French that we have this--

00:06:05.898 --> 00:06:08.434
it's what you call
solidarity, right?

00:06:08.434 --> 00:06:10.103
But, you know, it's history.

00:06:10.103 --> 00:06:11.738
You know, you can
either use it for you

00:06:11.738 --> 00:06:13.206
or use it against you, right.

00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:14.807
In this case, you're
saying, well, we

00:06:14.807 --> 00:06:18.077
have this mutual,
common interest

00:06:18.077 --> 00:06:21.347
based on our similar languages,
and let's call it Kreyolofoni,

00:06:21.347 --> 00:06:25.485
and let's turn it into
a political power.

00:06:25.485 --> 00:06:29.188
It's very idealistic,
but, you know, why not?

00:06:29.188 --> 00:06:32.425
AUDIENCE: So what about like
not describing it, like, people,

00:06:32.425 --> 00:06:35.361
but what about within
linguists, using the term

00:06:35.361 --> 00:06:39.966
creole to classify
languages that originated

00:06:39.966 --> 00:06:43.669
through a colonization process?

00:06:43.669 --> 00:06:46.239
Like, should that
space stay the same?

00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:48.541
MICHEL DEGRAFF: Well, no,
because now in science,

00:06:48.541 --> 00:06:50.176
you can read the
final terms, right?

00:06:50.176 --> 00:06:51.077
So this is different.

00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.845
So when you're
doing science, it's

00:06:52.845 --> 00:06:55.448
like when, you know-- so
H2O, water, for a chemist

00:06:55.448 --> 00:06:58.985
is not water for a gardener.

00:06:58.985 --> 00:07:03.189
So a gardener will use
water to sprinkle flowers

00:07:03.189 --> 00:07:05.925
without thinking about
the structure of water,

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:07.660
but if you're a
chemist, the word water

00:07:07.660 --> 00:07:09.362
has a different meaning
for you, and you

00:07:09.362 --> 00:07:11.931
might want to define what you
mean by water in that case.

00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:16.135
So it's just in linguistics, I
think that you can say, well,

00:07:16.135 --> 00:07:19.005
I'm going to use creole
with a particular sense.

00:07:19.005 --> 00:07:20.706
And for me, it's just so--

00:07:20.706 --> 00:07:22.942
you know, I'm going to
point to these languages

00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:25.445
with the people call who
them creole, who speak them,

00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:27.280
and I'm going to use
the name that they use.

00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:28.748
But I'm not going
to assume that it

00:07:28.748 --> 00:07:32.018
means something similar for
all creole languages, you see?

